@node "SuperWorm211" " Reviewing SuperWorm V2.11 "

<============================================================================>
     @{b}SuperWorm V2.11@{ub}                                  By: @{"Kari Suvivaara" link "Editor1"}
<============================================================================>

DESCRIPTION

   SuperWorm is a classical worm-style game. The idea is to eat little squares. You'll get points for each square you get, and if you do it quickly you'll get even more points. After eating each of them, you'll grow longer. If you hit the walls or yourself, you die.

FEATURES

 - Runs in a own window on the Workbench screen, in any screen mode.
 - Automatic window scaling depending on current screen mode/resolution.
 - Four differents window sizes to choose from.
 - No 90 degree steering
 - Detail level low/high for slower/faster Amigas.
 - Nice music (with is, btw, bigger than the executable :)
 - Shrinker and doubler squares
 - Highscore table
 - For 1 or 2 players at once
 - Automatic pausing when you deselect the window.

REQUIREMENTS

The game will run on any Amiga running Workbench 1.3 or better.

DISTRIBUTABILITY

It is FreeWare, and therefore you can copy it freely.

AVAILABILITY

The game is available from any Aminet site. e.g.

ftp://ftp.wustl.edu/pub/aminet/game/wb/SuperWorm211.lha

AUTHOR

Jouko Pynnönen - pynjo@jytol.fi

@{"Screenshot" system "Xtreme01:Pics/VT2 Xtreme01:Pics/SuperWorm.pic >NIL:"}

SuperWorm author, @{"Jouko Pynnönen" link "Jouko"}, at the interview!
