@node "Jouko" " Interviewing SuperWorm's author, Jouko Pynnönen "

<============================================================================>
  @{b}Interview: Jouko Pynnönen, author of SuperWorm V2.11@{ub}   By: @{"Kari Suvivaara" link "Editor1"}
<============================================================================>

   1. Age, length and weight?
Age is 21 years, length probably between 170 - 180 cm, weight probably at this moment between 60 - 70 kilos.

   2. Where did you get the idea to write SuperWorm?
All started from an impulse: one night I decided to do C-languaged program. After thinking for a while I decided to make a wormgame and something made me to do the steering free, not 90 degrees like in "normal" wormgames.

   3. What programming language did you use in SuperWorm?
At the first night made C-languaged version I translated to pure assembly after noticing the game getting slow dramaticly with pure-A500.

   4. What Amiga do you have?
Amiga 1200/030/FPU 68881, 2 MB CHIP + 4 MB FAST

   5. Why do you support Amiga, why not PC?
For some reason I haven't get used to PC (Windows) environment. It's also a habit question (continuing crashing, lagging, clumsyness, etc. isn't very easy to get used to after using the Amiga ;). Things when I need to use a computer (composing music, programming ja many others), computer's purpose is to be a helpful thing, not vice versa. This is the reason why I like Amiga better than PC.

   6. Other game/programs?
More or less not-completed projects can be found whole group, SuperWorm is still the only product which have been released.

   7. Plans for future?
There aren't any - production will maybe continue on not-planning-at-all; There aren't any signs for stopping in sight. There are some ideas (for example SuperWorm III) and I try to make them on my resources.

   8. Greetings?
Home of course and all friends. ;) And something to readers: We live hard times, but there is light in the end of the tunnel. Is that then PC-machine which you will buy in the future? You can think that for example during playing SuperWorm and hoping for best.
@endnode
@node "Riku" " Interviewing Ampu's author, Riku Rakkola "

<============================================================================>
    @{b}Interview: Riku Rakkola, author of Ampu V1.01@{ub}      By: @{"Kari Suvivaara" link "Editor1"}
<============================================================================>

   1. Age, lenght and weight?
Age: 17 years  Length: 185 cm  Weight: 70 kg

   2. Where did you get your idea to Ampu?
I planned originally to make normal artillery game, but project was delayed and I played Worms at my friends and I got lots of good ideas...and Worms-clone was born...but at least I learned to code on that very project.

   3. Why did you choose BlitzBasic and Assember to your programming languages?
I started Amiga programming on Amos, but because that language started to feel slow and limited I decided to get myself BlitzBasic, because I saw RoketzPD which is made by it, so I thought that can be good language. Assembler came little later when I needed more speed to certain parts and BB was good, because you can add straightly Assembler commands to BB.

   4. What is your Amiga?
A1200 + Blizzard 030/50 MHz + 16 MB, 520 MB HD and 28800bps modem

   5. Why are you supporting Amiga, why don't you support PC?
Amiga is very system friendly computer for it's operation system. Programming on Amiga is also easy, because there are much programming languages. The reason why I didn't bought PC is that all my friends got PC and I'm already had enough for that machine ;)

   6. Have you made other games/programs?
Ampu is my first BlitzBasic game, Amos "junk" I haven't never spread and I haven't done any programs.

   7. Plans for future?
There will be follow-up for Ampu, on the other hand follow-up is bad word for that, because game will be different from Worms and Ampu quite a lot. I can reveal that game will be placed on the Middle Ages, blood flies on it and there are computer monsters in it and there are extra effects for example water where can you swim etc. ;)

   8. Greetings?
All the dudes in #AmigaFIN, Haukka and all the members on Sulpu.
@endnode
