   My name is Ahti Komu and I live in Finland. I lived my childhood in Nastola. That's a city 23km east from Lahti. I got keyboards when I was 4. I didn't have any friends then. A girl who lived above us thought me how to play my keyboards.

   At the time only friend I had was my keyboard. That's why I nowadays am a very good pianist. But, when I was 6 we moved to Reisjärvi. Now, that's a small town. I lived there and again was teased by other kids.

   From there we moved to here Haapajärvi where I live now. Here I also was teased by other kids until highschool. But I tried to live with that teasing and joined a band where everyone teased me and eventually I parted from it.

   After this I was in another band but our mixer broke up and eventually so did our band. Now in highschool people are smart enough to not to tease me =). I've gotten a few friends and everything is starting to seem to fine.

   For now I have composed about 200 songs for piano and about 250 songs for Amiga. I bought my Amiga at the summer '95 and since then I've composed almost every day. I have noticed I have an excellent numbermemory.

   Because of that I can calculate VERY fast. I also have a great tunememory which allows me to play almost every song after one or two hearing. I like almost every style of music. Metal, ballads, jazz, classics, rock etc. Almost everything goes...few exceptions are for example tango, waltz and march.

   My hobbies are: playing piano, computers (composing, programming, playing, IRC) and watching TV (luckily we have a cable-TV which allows to have 12 channels).

   At the time I am doing a game. It will maybe be ready after an year. But, I'm not doing it alone. I'm coding it and making it's musics and a danish guy is making it's graphics (thanks Folcka).

